verbs.description: muzz (third-person singular simple present muzzes, present participle muzzing, simple past and past participle muzzed)

entries.meaning: (slang, now rare) To study intently; to pore over. [from 18th c.]
(slang, obsolete) To hang around aimlessly; to loiter. [18th c.]
examples: ‘If You but knew, cried I, to whom I am going to Night! and who I shall see to Night! – you would not dare keep me muzzing here!’

entries.meaning: (slang) To make muzzy or hazy; to confuse. [from 18th c.]
